        <li>Active development and frequent updates</li>
        <li>Growing community and ecosystem</li>
        
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3>Asana Cons</h3>
    <div class="cons-box">
      <ul>
        <li>Less visually engaging</li>
        <li>Fewer automation recipes</li>
        <li>Timeline view less intuitive</li>
        <li>Steeper learning curve</li>
        <li>Higher per-seat cost</li>
        <li>Interface can feel overwhelming initially</li>
        <li>Premium features require higher tier plans</li>
        
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>Who Should Use Which?</h2>
    <p><strong>Choose Monday.com</strong> if you want a visual intuitive project management tool with strong automation.</p>
    <p><strong>Choose Asana</strong> if you need detailed task management, portfolio tracking, and larger teams.</p>

